  "texts": [
    "That is, in real-world applications, estimates of consumers' personality from digital traces might contain substantial amounts of prediction error, or could become outdated over time.",
    "We conducted both between and within-subjects analyses (see Table S33 for zero-order correlations).",
    "The between-subjects analyses compared participants' evaluations of the first ad they rated for each product using linear regression models.",
    "In line with our expectations, participants who were shown a personalized weekend getaway ad rated the ad as significantly more effective (B = 0.43, β = 0.31, CI 95 0.08-0.53, p = 0.008) and were willing to spend a significantly larger amount of money on the trip (B = 116.57, β = 0.24, CI 95 0.01-0.47, p = 0.037) than those who were shown the generic version.",
    "Specifically, the personalized ads increased people's willingness to spend by $117."
  ],
